title: MUSA 5080 Portfolio
text:
This portfolio documents my learning journey in Public Policy Analytics (MUSA 5080).


Advanced spatial analysis and data science for urban planning and public policy.




Weekly Notes: My learning reflections and key concepts
Labs: Completed assignments and analyses
Final Project: Capstone modeling challenge




Lay’la Harmon, B.A Sociology and Leadership Studies - M.A Candidate City Planning layharmon@gmail.com - harmon1@upenn.edu Github Username: layharm As a HCED student, I find the ability to piviot into different fields to be imperitve. I am taking this course to challenge myself, I hope to use the tools I learn here in my career going forward.
